  "title": "Lead Product Manager",
  "description": "<p>Join a mission-driven team tackling some of the most complex technology challenges across industries.</p><p>Our team blends deep product, engineering, and design expertise to reimagine how systems work — building scalable, human-centered solutions that deliver lasting impact.</p><p><strong>What You’ll Be Working On</strong></p><ul><li>Lead end-to-end product engagements — from discovery and strategy through to roadmap definition and implementation planning</li><li>Align product direction with business goals, user needs, and technical realities</li><li>Act as a strategic partner to clients, guiding them through ambiguity and complexity</li><li>Champion modern product and engineering practices that drive measurable outcomes</li><li>Mentor and grow product managers and cross-functional teams</li><li>Represent the practice in industry forums, communities of practice, and thought leadership spaces</li></ul><p><strong>You’ll Thrive Here If You:</strong></p><ul><li>Enjoy making sense of complex, ambiguous challenges</li><li>Translate technical concepts into clear, human language</li><li>Focus on outcomes and long-term value, not just deliverables</li><li>Influence through trust, clarity, and collaboration</li><li>Love working at the problem-definition stage</li></ul><p><strong>What We’re Looking For:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 8 years of product manager experience, with a track record of leading complex initiatives</li><li>Strong systems thinking and ability to connect strategy to execution</li><li>Deep fluency in agile, product discovery, user research, and iterative delivery</li><li>Excellent facilitation and communication skills; comfortable with C-suite</li><li>Proven ability to influence across organizational boundaries</li><li>Entrepreneurial mindset with a drive to build, improve, and create meaningful impact</li></ul><p>For more information you can contact <em>Norean Tan at norean.tan@sanderson-ikas.sg</em></p><p>We regret to inform you that only shortlisted candidates will be notified / contacted.</p><p>EA Registration No.: R1434118 <em>- Tan Lee Ying, Norean</em></p><p>iKas International (Asia) Pte Ltd</p><p>ROC No.: 200914065E | EA License No.: 16S8086</p>",
